<p><b>History</b></p>
<ul><b>1914</b> – Born on February 8</ul>
<ul><b>1939</b> – Bill Finger was brought on to help Bob Kane with writing Batman</ul>
<ul><b>1940</b> – Co-created The Joker in <a href='http://batman.wikia.com/wiki/Batman_Issue_1' target=blank>Batman #1</a></ul>
<ul><b>1949</b> – wrote the Superman(bold)  teenage-love interest character Lana Lang</ul>
<ul><b>1961</b> – wrote the Batman(bold) character Clayface in Detective Comics #298(bold)</ul>
<ul><b>1974</b> – dies at the age of 59)</ul></p>

<p><ul><b>1994</b> – inducted into the Will Eisner Comic Book Hall of Fame</ul>
<ul><b>1999</b> –inducted into the comic book industry’s Jack Kirby Hall of Fame<ul></p>
